<h4>What is Whole Planet Foundation?</h4>
Whole Planet Foundation’s mission is poverty alleviation through microcredit in communities around the world that supply Whole Foods Market stores with products.<br /><br />

The Foundation was founded in 2005 and has generated $50.9 million in microloans.<br /><br />

<h4>What is microcredit?</h4>
Microcredit (aka “microfinance”) encapsulates a wide array of products and services from credit to savings that are designed to meet the needs of the world’s un- and underbanked. Whole Planet Foundation focuses on the credit component of microfinance and seeks partners that have a mission to and a methodology that is able to reach the most marginalized groups of micro-entrepreneurs. Some of the key characteristics of microcredit supported by Whole Planet Foundation:<br /><br />

<ul>
<li>Focus on the poorest microentrepreneurs possible, especially women</li>
<li>No collateral or guarantees will be required</li>
<li>The banking services will be provided to the people as close to their doorstep as possible</li>
<li>Loan transactions are transparent at all levels</li>
<li>Loan sizes will grow with each loan cycle</li>
<li>The borrowers will be free to choose to participate</li>
<li>Repayments will be designed in a way that meets the needs of the borrower</li>
<li>There will be the fewest barriers to entry possible for people with little to no assets</li>
</ul>

<h4>Why does Rishi Support Whole Planet Foundation?</h4>
As an entrepreneurial direct-trade tea company, we share many values with Whole Planet Foundation. We consider the farmers we work with as our partners; their livelihoods, community development and environmental preservation are crucial factors for our mutual success. Rishi shares Whole Planet Foundation's goal of empowering partners to create their own success. Firsthand experiences with our partners across the globe has convinced all of us at Rishi that microcredit can help facilitate growth and prosperity for our partners, and friends.<br /><br />

It is our honor and privilege to be able to support Whole Planet Foundation at the $50,000 “Supplier Alliance” level for the third year in a row. <br /><br />

<h4>Rishi’s Impact</h4>
Since joining the Supplier Alliance for Microcredit  in 2014, Rishi has committed $150,000 to Whole Planet Foundation.<br /><br />

To date, our commitment has generated 800 microns, helping to alleviate poverty for 4,000 people worldwide. <br /><br />

